                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/9318.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister to Belgium</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-10-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 22, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s October 14, 7 p.m. The Belgian Government, as a secondary and
                    neutral power, is prevented by traditional policy from comment thereon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marburg</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
